<subSubSection id="0BFDC3E62E15FFEE63D5FA0DFAA6F8CA" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4358906D2E15FFEE63D5FA0DFDFEF961" blockId="1.[151,1437,1429,1866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE63D5FA0DFEADFA3A" bold="true" box="[198,320,1466,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the original description 
<bibRefCitation id="2776ED9C2E15FFEE6193FA0DFC06FA3A" author="Bader" box="[640,1003,1466,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgosarian, H. (1982) Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran. 14. Mitteilung: Zwei weitere Arten aus der Untergattung Mixosperchon (Sperchonidae). Entomologische Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Hamburg, 7 (116), 219 - 232." type="journal article" year="1982">
Bader &amp; Sepasgosarian (
<number id="F52F824A2E15FFEE60B6FA0DFC0FFA3A" box="[933,994,1466,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<taxonomicName id="84E7EBEE2E15FFEE677DFA0CFA8DFA3A" box="[1134,1376,1467,1492]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE677DFA0CFA8DFA3A" box="[1134,1376,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Sperchon bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="84E7EBEE2E15FFEE6384FA57FEDBFA17" box="[151,310,1504,1529]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papillosus">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE6384FA57FEDBFA17" box="[151,310,1504,1529]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. papillosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, separating these two species only by the measurements of the palps. A re-examination of specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="84E7EBEE2E15FFEE6224F9B2FE22F9F0" box="[311,463,1541,1566]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE6224F9B2FE22F9F0" box="[311,463,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<typeStatus id="9C5C2ECF2E15FFEE6153F9B2FD9EF9F1" box="[576,627,1541,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
series shows that from all points of view (integument sculpture made up of a network of fine denticles combined with additional larger papillae and the similar shape of dorsum and palp) these specimens are in close agreement with 
<taxonomicName id="84E7EBEE2E15FFEE61EAF9E7FC7CF987" box="[761,913,1616,1641]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papillosus">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE61EAF9E7FC7CF987" box="[761,913,1616,1641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. papillosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus 
<taxonomicName id="84E7EBEE2E15FFEE60F6F9E7FB6FF987" box="[997,1154,1616,1641]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE60F6F9E7FB6FF987" box="[997,1154,1616,1641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="84E7EBEE2E15FFEE6265F9C2FDE0F960" box="[374,525,1653,1678]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papillosus">
<emphasis id="71934C7F2E15FFEE6265F9C2FDE0F960" box="[374,525,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">S. papillosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
